<title>UK: Mirror Group plans costs savings - paper.</title>
<headline>Mirror Group plans costs savings - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mirror Group Plc is to launch a retraining exercise for several hundred newspaper production staff aimed at cutting costs by several million pounds, according to a report in the Financial Times.</p>
<p>The company said the main object would be to allow staff to take responsibility for whole pages rather than just text or headlines, the FT said, quoting MGN chief executive David Montgomery as saying the revolution in Britain's newpaper industry was &quot;not over yet.&quot;</p>
<p>Earlier MGN reported annual results showing pre-tax pre-exceptional profits rising to 82.2 million stg from 77.1 million a year before.</p>
